The paper discusses signal recovery in compressive sensing, which is a topic that falls under multiple sub-categories of arXiv CS. The use of sparsity in multiple domains suggests that the paper could belong to cs.IT (Information Theory) or cs.SP (Signal Processing). The use of convex programming also suggests that the paper could belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the use of a priori information suggests that the paper could belong to cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
